# Project: AI Task Tracker

Personal task tracker. Users write tasks in natural language;
GPT-4o-mini parses them into structured fields. Deployed on Vercel.

## Stack
Next.js 15 App Router · TypeScript strict · Tailwind · Prisma · Neon
Postgres · NextAuth v5 (Google) · OpenAI · next-intl · Google Calendar API.

## Non-negotiable rules

### Internationalization (i18n)
- UI is bilingual: Ukrainian (default) + English toggle
- NEVER hardcode user-visible text in components
- Every string lives in `messages/uk.json` and `messages/en.json`
- When you add a new string, add it to BOTH files in the same PR
- Use next-intl `useTranslations()` (client) or `getTranslations()` (server)
- Translation keys are namespaced: `tasks.addButton`, `auth.signInWithGoogle`

### Theming
- Light + dark mode via Tailwind `darkMode: "class"` strategy
- All colors come from CSS variables defined on `:root` and `.dark`
- NEVER use raw hex / Tailwind color names like `bg-red-500` for theme colors
- Use semantic tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`,
  `bg-primary`, `bg-destructive`, etc. (shadcn convention)
- Theme provider must read system preference on first mount; respect
  user override after that; persist to localStorage

### TypeScript
- Strict mode on. No `any` without a written reason in a comment.
- Validate ALL external data with Zod: AI responses, form inputs,
  env vars, API route bodies.
- Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when you need
  state, effects, or browser APIs.

### Data flow
- Mutations through Server Actions, not API routes (unless needed for
  external webhooks like Google Calendar push notifications)
- Every mutation: validate input → check session → write to DB →
  revalidate path → return typed result

### Security
- Every Server Action and route handler checks `auth()` first
- `userId` is always taken from the session, never from the client
- Never log secrets; never commit `.env*` files
- Google Calendar tokens are encrypted at rest (NextAuth handles this
  if configured correctly)

### File structure
- `app/[locale]/...` — all routes wrapped in locale segment
- `components/ui/` — reusable primitives (button, input, dialog, ...)
- `components/features/` — feature-specific components
- `lib/` — db client, auth config, openai client, gcal client, utils
- `lib/actions/` — Server Actions, one file per feature
- `lib/schemas/` — Zod schemas
- `messages/uk.json`, `messages/en.json`
- `prisma/schema.prisma`

### Conventions
- Code comments in English; commit messages in English
- File names kebab-case; components PascalCase; functions camelCase
- Prefer named exports
- Reuse existing utilities in `lib/` before writing new ones —
  ALWAYS grep first

## After every change you make
1. List changed files
2. Note any new translation keys added (must exist in both uk.json and en.json)
3. Note any new env vars (must be added to env validation + .env.example)
4. State what I should manually test